CAPE TOWN - The man accused of killing a 13-year-old in Klawer in the Western Cape, has confessed to the boy's murder. The man's lawyer Santie Human has confirmed this to eNCA. eNCA’s Ronald Masinda reports. Courtesy #DStv403 #eNCA The man will appear in court on Monday. He was arrested after the remains of the boy were found in his drain on Friday. [Warning: Some viewers may find these visuals disturbing] The man accused of killing a 13-year-old in Klawer in the Western Cape has confessed to the boy's murder. The man's lawyer Santie Human has confirmed this to eNCA. The man will appear in court tomorrow. #DStv403 pic.twitter.com/GRq1zvWdw5